# Best Practices

Organizations implementing Clauses 8–10 should:

- Conduct Business Impact Analyses regularly.
- Review business continuity risks annually or after significant changes.
- Develop practical and easy-to-use Business Continuity Plans.
- Perform regular exercises involving both technical and business teams.
- Monitor BCMS performance using measurable KPIs and KRIs.
- Conduct independent internal audits.
- Hold management reviews at planned intervals.
- Implement corrective actions and continuously improve the BCMS.

Following these practices ensures that the Business Continuity Management System remains operationally effective, audit-ready, and capable of supporting organizational resilience in the face of evolving threats and disruptions.

---

# Practical Example

A multinational cloud service provider has fully implemented its ISO 22301 Business Continuity Management System across global operations.

Under **Clause 8**, the company performs annual Business Impact Analyses (BIAs), updates continuity strategies for its regional data centers, maintains Business Continuity Plans for all critical services, and conducts quarterly disaster recovery simulations involving technical and business teams. During **Clause 9**, internal auditors review BCMS compliance, management monitors Recovery Time Objectives (RTOs), Recovery Point Objectives (RPOs), and service availability metrics, and executive leadership conducts formal management reviews to evaluate overall BCMS performance.

Following a large-scale cloud outage, post-incident reviews identify improvements in communication procedures and failover automation. Under **Clause 10**, the organization updates continuity plans, enhances employee training, improves supplier resilience requirements, and introduces new performance metrics. Through this continual improvement cycle, the company strengthens its resilience, maintains customer confidence, and ensures that its BCMS remains effective as technologies, business operations, and external risks continue to evolve.


